  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM1.11">
<l>tiṭarviḷaṅku karaippoṉṉi naṭuvu pāṭṭut</l>
<l>tiruvaraṅkat taravaṇaiyiṟ paḷḷi koḷḷum</l>
<l>kaṭalviḷaṅku karumēṉi yammāṉ ṟaṉṉaik</l>
<l>kaṇṇārak kaṇṭukakkuṅ kātal taṉṉāl</l>
<l>kuṭaiviḷaṅku viṟaṟṟāṉaik koṟṟa voḷvāḷ</l>
<l>kūṭalarkōṉ koṭaikkulacē karaṉcoṟ ceyta</l>
<l>naṭaiviḷaṅku tamiḻmālai pattum vallār</l>
<l>nalantikaḻnā raṇaṉaṭikkīḻ naṇṇu vārē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master</l>
<l rend="indent">all ten [songs] in the Tamil garland brilliant in rhythm,</l>
<l rend="indent">worded by the munificent Kulacēkaraṉ, king of the people of Kūṭal</l>
<l rend="indent">—who shines with a [royal] parasol, a victorious army and a sword glowing with victory—</l>
<l rend="indent">out of the desire to rejoice, having seen to the satisfaction of [his] eyes</l>
<l rend="indent">the Lord with a dark-hued body that shines [like] the ocean,</l>
<l rend="indent">who sleeps on the serpent-bed in Śrīraṅgam,</l>
<l rend="indent">in the middle of the Poṉṉi with banks that shines with islets,</l>
<l>shall reach below the feet of Nārāyaṇa shining with goodness.</l>

      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
